SIMPLE: scaly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scaly
<hw>Scal"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered or
abounding with scales; <as>as, a <ex>scaly</ex> fish</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Scaly</xex> crocodile.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resembling scales, laminae, or layers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Mean; low; <as>as, a <ex>scaly</ex>
fellow</as>.</def> <mark>[Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Composed of scales lying over each
other; <as>as, a <ex>scaly</ex> bulb</as>; covered with scales; <as>as,
a <ex>scaly</ex> stem</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Scaly ant-eater</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
pangolin.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scaly-winged</ent>⟦br⟧
